The paper deals with a problem of labeling points in a dynamic map that allows rotation, which involves computational geometry (cs.CG) and graphics (cs.GR). The paper also discusses and evaluates several labeling models that define additional consistency constraints on label activities, which involves algorithms and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper experimentally compares different heuristic algorithms, which involves data structures (cs.DS) and computer vision (cs.CV).
